.TH "snd_pcm_lib_preallocate_pages_for_all" 9 "snd_pcm_lib_preallocate_pages_for_all" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_lib_preallocate_pages_for_all \- pre-allocation for continuous memory type (all substreams)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_pcm_lib_preallocate_pages_for_all
.BI "(struct snd_pcm *pcm "  ","
.BI "int type "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
the pcm instance
.IP "type" 12
DMA type (SNDRV_DMA_TYPE_*)
.IP "data" 12
DMA type dependent data
.IP "size" 12
the requested pre-allocation size in bytes
.IP "max" 12
the max. allowed pre-allocation size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Do pre-allocation to all substreams of the given pcm for the
specified DMA type.
